**Title: Precision Mapping of Parameter Recovery Limits in Underdamped Systems**

This study aims to quantify the robustness of Bayesian parameter estimation against Gaussian measurement noise across the 20 provided oscillator profiles. By implementing a non-linear least squares optimization to recover the `damping_coefficient` ($b$) and `natural_frequency` ($\omega$) from the noisy `displacement` and `velocity` time series, we will establish the convergence precision of the physical model parameters. The research will specifically map the recovery error—defined as the deviation from the provided ground truth parameters—as a continuous function of the `damping_ratio`. By systematically evaluating these error surfaces, we will identify the specific threshold of the `damping_ratio` where measurement noise compromises the identifiability of the underdamped system. This approach transforms the dataset from a simple signal source into a benchmark for assessing the sensitivity of white-box physical models to inherent stochastic fluctuations.
\end{IDEA}


